headline: This Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stock Soared Since Trump Won the Election, but Is It a Buy?
summary: In the days following Donald Trump's return to the White House, the stock market has set record highs.  While Trump has promised to cut taxes and boost business, he's also expressed his desire to regulate certain big tech players, and his tariff-based trade policy could affect the artificial intelligence (AI) companies that rely on foreign-made components.  Palantir (NYSE: PLTR), in particular, saw its stock pop dramatically after Election Day, which was the day after Palantir issued its quarterly earnings.
